8. Create and invoke the get_sal function with a single input parameter to return the salary of the inputted employee.

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION get_sal
(p_id employees.employee_id%TYPE) RETURN NUMBER IS
v_sal employees.salary%TYPE := 0;
BEGIN
SELECT salary
INTO v_sal
FROM employees
WHERE employee_id = p_id;
RETURN v_sal;
END get_sal;
/
```

```sql
EXEC DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE(get_sal(100))
```

9. Create and invoke the TAX function with a single input parameter to return the income tax based simple flat tax rate for the inputted salary.

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION tax(p_value IN NUMBER)
RETURN NUMBER IS
BEGIN
RETURN (p_value * 0.08);
END tax;
/
SELECT employee_id, last_name, salary, tax(salary)
FROM employees
WHERE department_id = 100;
```

10. Create and invoke the GET_JOB function to return a job title.

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION get_job
(p_jobid IN jobs.job_id%TYPE)
RETURN
jobs.job_title%TYPE
IS
v_jobtitle jobs.job_title%TYPE;
BEGIN
SELECT job_title
INTO v_jobtitle
FROM jobs
WHERE job_id = p_jobid;
RETURN v_jobtitle;
END get_job;
/
EXEC DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE(get_job('ST_MAN'));
```

11. Create a function called GET_ANNUAL_COMP to return the annual salary computed from the employeeâ€™s monthly salary and commission passed as parameters.

```sql
create or replace function get_annual_comp
(p_sal IN employees.salary%type,
p_comm IN employees.commission_pct%type)
return number 
IS
begin
return(nvl(p_sal,0) * 12 + (nvl(p_comm,0) * 12));
end;
/
```

```sql
select employee_id, last_name, 
get_annual_comp(salary, commission_pct) "Annual Compensation"
from employees
where department_id=30;
```

12) Create a procedure ADD_EMPLOYEE to insert a new employee into the EMPLOYEES table. The procedure should call a VALID_DEPTID function to check whether the department_id for the new employee exists in the DEPARTMENTS table.
